@node intro " VoteX v1.52 -- Introduction -- "

 VoteX v1.52, is, as a matter of fact, a quickly growing Daydream voting
door, it has been designed to offer users MaXiMuM options & selections,
making it the BeSt voting door on the Amiga ( And most other platforms ).

 VoteX has gone through a lot right from the first release right back in
January 24th 1998, just to show how commited I am to produce the BeSt stuff I
can for Daydream BBS, I've worked hard on this door, and will continue to do
so, as long as I get the feedback & suggestions . I've got some feedback from
various people all around europe, regarding my first version of VoteX, most
of which were complaints and bug reports . But I made sure most of them got
the newer versions, with tons of bugs fixed. That's when the complaints
started disappearing, and have been replaced with suggestions and people that
wanted part of VoteX . By then I realised that I have to be a bit more strict
rather than my previous `happy-go-lucky' attitude, that was in a way the
reason I was slightly harsh towards a lot of people . Anyhow, the lack of
BETA testers was the main problem, I have to BETA test the stuff myself
mostly . I know that some people that are reading this ( You guys that wrote )
will complain that I didn't send them up-to-date versions of this door, but
hey, some didn't even suggest or do anything with the previous versions ! And
that's why I had to be harsh in a way, lots of people say they want to BETA
test, but all they do is get the program off me and check it out once or
twice, and the rest is history .... I hope you guys understand the real
meaining of BETA testing, iow, just smash the program as hard as you can, try
to find the bugs, let them out, and report them . So, checkout the BETA
tester request ..

 Anyway, VoteX has been a pleasure working on, and I will continue to put a
lot of effort into it's forthcoming versions . 


                        --- On With The Show ---

 


@endnode

@node new "  VoteX v1.52 -- What's New -- "

 Since the last released version quite a lot, you can check the History for
that, but the changes related to this version aren't many ...

First, the new menu is a lot nicer, the old one was very wEiRd and a lot of
people hated it, some of which suggested to make the ANSIs for me, but most
of them didn't understand why the ANSI I made sucked, it was because I CAN
NOT PUT A CHARECTER AFTER THE DAMN SUBJECT ! ELSE, WITH EACH SUBJECT THE
CHARECTER WILL MOVE !!! Now, I don't know if you understood that, but whether
you do, or don't, I don't care ...

Other than the ANSIs, the size has decreased dramatically, just past 12Kb .
Considering that v0.92 was just over 14Kb, well, that version was a rush, I
didn't care about keeping the file small. As for this version, I have started
work on the `optimization' part, I will try to make VoteX smaller all the
time, it will be tough, and don't suspect to end up with a door under 10K,
because from now on the minimum size of VoteX will be 13K+ . 

 Some slight mini-tincy little bugs fixed, mostly text errors ... But that
has been taken care of .
@endnode


@node Install " VoteX v1.52 -- Installation -- "

 Unlike the previous VoteX release, this one has a two cute installer scripts
for you all, even though surprisingly, no-one suggested it ! Oh well .


 System Requirements :
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

 A1200 onwards ... ( didn't test it on A500 or A600 )

 Daydream v1.27 onwards ( didn't test it on previous versions )

 Some ram ... The standard 2Mb Chip is fine ...

 Harddisk .. Well, that's for Daydream, not neccesarily VoteX ..


 Installation
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~

 If you had a previous version of VoteX (iow, v0.92) then you can select
restore152 to install the new version, and restore all the data from the old
version ( nice eh ? ) . Or select Install152 if you want to install it for
new . Then you'll have to alter you're external Commands I guess .. Add a
line like :

Doors:Rexx %N doors:votex/votex152.dd

That should do it ...


 Or you can install the enitre thing manually by making a directory in DOORS:
called VoteX, then copy all the files in the archive to it and add the
previous line to the external thinige ...



 I hope the scripts made the hassle less in away, ;)


@endnode

