@node bugs " VoteX v1.52 -- Known Bugs --

 Well, so far only one known bug ...

 The Node sometimes crashes mysteriously when changing the subject, if it
happens to YOU, then just restart the computer or Node ( if possible ) and
change it, it should be fixed . WeiRd BuG .

 If you do find any other, do you're thing and contact me .




@endnode

@node future " VoteX v1.52 -- Future VoteX Releases -- "

 Well, I've decided that everone that drops me a line shal recieve the
unreleased versions which will be from v1.53 till v1.59, which will be under
the theme of `optimization' I will try to optimize the code as much as I can
in those versions .

 VoteX v1.9 or so will include `themes', allowing more than one subject to be
voted on, maybe three, but I'm considering five . I'll also make a few
changes like the enability for the users to see who voted for what, and will
keep that only for the SysOp . I'm also looking into making the the Vote
Count show the votes in percentage rather than number .

 VoteX v2.0, well this version most probably will be a re-write, ten times
more optimized version, and will have the same features, and a few other new
things like :

 * Checking to see if a specified user is online .
 
 * Two end confrontation option, allows to confront each other, semi-dialoge
style, and allows everyone to see it .

 * New quicker subject changing techniques ( could be implemented in earlier
versions )

 So far that's it . But if you have any suggestions, then drop me a line, and
remember, You're suggestions will hopefully be implemented sooner rather than
later, most probably by version 2.0, as I said that version will be a remake
of the entire door .



@endnode


@node history " VoteX v1.52 -- VoteX History -- "


  The History of VoteX, the Voting door for Daydream BBS .


VoteX v0.50 (Not released)

 The initial structure for VoteX, only creates a log for votes, and a
`Built-in' subject.


VoteX v0.92 (Released)

 Major changes, first being the inclusion of views, for and against . The
voting procedure changed slightly, as two file (1 for & 1 against) to
seperate both voters . External Subject file, to make the SysOp change the
subject at his/her will . And the original MENU

VoteX v1.1 (Not released)

 The inclusion of the SysOp menu to make the changing of the subject &
SysOp's view as simple as possible, iow, got rid of the hassle the SysOp has
to go through just to create a new subject .

VoteX v1.5 (Not released)

 The major implementation in this version is the enability for the user to
vote more than once, which was the problem from version 0.92 onwards . Also,
all the files for VoteX have been moved into their own directory, makes life
a lot easier when looking for files, a lot easier . Also, new installer
scripts added to ease installation .

VoteX v1.52 (Released)

 Newer ANSIs, and a slightly more optimized code, however, still bigger than
previous versions . Small forgotten thing regarding SysOp view when changing
the subject, now fixed . Plan for subject menu in the future


@endnode

@node ME " VoteX v1.52 -- About The Author -- "

 I don't know why I put this really, but oh well, some people out there might
be interested .

 Well, according to the release date, my sixteenth birthday just passed two
days ago, on th 18th . I am a sixteen year old Amiga ~ Daydream fanatic .
I've been working on tons of doors since the end of January `98 ( Less than 
a month ago ) . And will hopefully continue to do so .

 Nothing much really to say, other than the fact that I'm going to hate
myself soon, very soon . Why ? Well, because there hasn't been a NotePad
Amiga released, if PAWS would release one then that'd be cool, I'm leaving to
Canada next year .  And I will not be able to take my Amiga with me, which
reminds me, my Amiga is an A1200 with an apollo card 030 25Mhz + 4Mb RAM,
soon to be 8Mb, and a nice cute 540Mb HD . I will continue to release
Daydream Doors no matter what ! But my parents don't want me taking my Amiga
with me, so I'll have to start saving some money so when I got Canada I can
perchase a keWl Note Pad Amiga, or even an Amiga on a card thingie, but then
the University there will kill me if I use it (damn!) . So ladies and
Gentelmen, if you want me to go through a few more years of door programing,
then please beg Amiga Int. to consider dumping a Note Pad or Lap Top Amiga
project on someone ;) . As long as it is PPC though ...

@EndNoDe

@Node beta " VoteX v1.52 -- BETA Testers request -- "

 If there is anyone out there that has used any of my doors, and would like
to see them grow, then he/she can help by being a BETA tester, if you do want
to become a BETA tester then all you have to do is abide by the following
regulations :

 * You shall recieve every new version of the door you have agreed to BETA
test .

 * You must report any bugs or errors with all appropreate details that you
think (or don't) are releated to the error .

 * You must suggest any ideas that you think should be implemented in future
versions of the door you are testing .

 * I will take no responsability in any damage caused to your computer,
whether caused by ignorence or carelessness, unless appropreate evidence that
proves the author to have done so, which only the author can judge upon .

 * Your name will be included in the credits and @{"special thanks" Link thanku} in the
release of the door, as long as you have contributed in any way to its
release .

 If you accept these rules than you are welcomed as an official BETA tester .
Else, that is entirely up to you .

@endnode

@node other " VoteX v1.52 -- Other Non-VoteX Releases -- "

 There is a series of other doors that I've already created and are more than
worth the download time from the Aminet .

 SToryC, a nice door for BBS with a decent amount of users. Every user adds a
line as part of a story, as the story grows it will become more and more
complete, and ten times the fun with every new line added . You can also
download the story and read it for yourself at any time !

 SS98, Soccer ShootOut `98, choose a goalkeeper, and start shooting away, see
how good you are when facing some of the world's toughest keepers.

 SU, Simpe door that is only 209 bytes in size !! It is put as a login door
that checks if the SysOp is available or not, and gives the reason for not
being available, very small, but at the same time very useful .

 Desc, Descussions, a nice descussions door that when combined with VoteX can
create miracles ! Allows the users to choose a subject and talk about it,
they can also suggest subjects, and download views . Great door .

 Friend, a weird door, just enter it and talk to the computer, all the
computer will do is listen though,

make sure you check out the latest versions of all these doors, as they will
constantly change, and also the decriptions here will also change with all
the newer versions . If you want to get the latest versions of these door,
whether to check them out or to be a BETA tester, just @{"contact the author"link contact}

 Other doors that are under development :

 LameC, a fake chat clone that with personalities and also creates log files
for all the conversations .

 Weirdo's Boxing, a boxing game with an attitude, direct comentary and
special moves too .

 Stoopid World, a text based adventure with TONS of ANSI graphics with it,
could be one of the best of its kind ! ( Contact the author if you would like
to help in this big door, all help would be apreciated ).

 MaD PaRtY, a great fun door that is almost finalized, includes invitation
lists, commenting, SPLATING, and tonsa stuff . Personally, I like this .


 This is what I'm working on so far, just make sure you contact me for all
the latest information on my doors, let me also remind you, a lot of doors
could appear out of nowhere without previous mentioning, so keep alert .


@endnode

